Still cannot link the tightness with MASS simd library.

For example this simple code
testv.c
-----
#include <mass_simdp7.h>
#include <altivec.h>

int main() {

  vector double a = {1, 3};
  vector double b = logd2(a);
  return 0;
}
-----

I cannot compile it in p7curielin  (MASS: I/opt/ibm/mass/6.0/sles10/)
or p7curielin2 (MASS: /opt/ibmcmp/xlmass/7.1/)

For example in p7curielin, 
neither xlc nor gcc works.

xlc -qaltivec -qarch=pwr7 -q64 -I/opt/ibm/mass/6.0/sles10/include -L/opt/ibm/mass/6.0/sles10/lib64 -lmass_simdp7_64 testv.c
    testv.o:(.text+0x30): undefined reference to `logd2'

gcc -m64 -mvsx -I/opt/ibm/mass/6.0/sles10/include -L/opt/ibm/mass/6.0/sles10/lib64 -lmass_simdp7_64 testv.c
/tmp/ccVxcNPa.o:(.text+0x30): undefined reference to `logd2'
collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status


The logd2 is defined in mass_simdp7.h and there is a symbol logd2 in libmass_simdp7_64.a

But I can compile it in AIX.